               The eight and twentieth Excuſe. How could I be ſaved
if Chriſt did not die for me? He died but for his Elect;
and none could be ſaved without his Death.

1. Things that Men highly value will be remembred,
they will be matter of their freeſt and ſweeteſt thoughts;
this a known Caſe.
